metatags.og:description:
I have been working as a Computer Scientist for more than 30 years, a University Professor for 25 years and a Data Scientist for around 13 years. A summary of my achievements and activities:

* 130+ papers and technical works published.
* 4,000+ students taught at different levels (BSc, MSc, PhD, CPD training).
* 60+ students supervised at different levels (BSc, MSc, PhD) and research projects.
* Secured research funding (as PI or Co-PI) from several companies and agencies, including Google, The Rockefeller Foundation, HDR UK, Medical Research Council, The Royal Society, Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, Wellcome Trust, Royal Academy of Engineering, NVIDIA, Santander, GCRF, CNPq.
* Visiting professor/researcher positions at Université Joseph Fourier (Grenoble, 2000) and Universitat Ramon Llull (Barcelona, 2002).
* Editorial board of the International Journal of Population Data Science (IJPDS).
* Fellow of the UK Higher Education Academy (FHEA).

More information at https://marcos
